92; Herault, J., Jutten, C., Space or time adaptive signal processing by neural network models (1986) Neural Networks For Computing: Aip Conference Proceedings, , Denker JS (ed.). American Institute for physics: New York; Horel, J.D., A rotated principal compoent analysis of the interannual varaibility of Northern Hemisphere 500 mb height field (1981) Monthly Weather Review, 109, pp. 2080-2902; Houghton, R.W., Tourre, Y.M., Characteristics of Low-frequency sea surface temperature fluctuations in the tropical Atlantic (1992) Journal of Climate, 5, pp. 765-771; Hsiung, J., Newell, R.E., The principal nonseasonal modes of variation of global sea surface temperature (1983) Journal of Physical Oceanography, 13, pp. 1957-1967; Hurrell, J.W., Decadal trends in the North Atlantic Oscillation: Regional temperature and precipitation (1995) Science, 269, pp. 676-679; Hyvarinen, A., Survey on independent component analysis (1999) Neural Computing Surveys, 2, pp. 94-128; Hyvarinen, A., Karhunen, J., Oja, E., (2001) Independent Component Analysis, p. 481. , John Wiley and Sons: New York; Ilin, A., Valpola, H., Oja, E., Exploratory analysis of climate data using source separation methods (2006) Neural Networks, 19, pp. 155-167; Janicot, S., Trzaska, S., Poccard, I., Summer Sahel-ENSO teleconnection and decadal time scale SST variations (2001) Climate Dynamics, 18, pp. 303-320; Jolliffe, I.T., Rotation of principal components: Some comments (1987) Journal of Climatology, 7, pp. 507-510; Jolliffe, I.T., A cautionary note on Artificial examples of EOFs (2003) Journal of Climate, 16 (7), pp. 1084-1086; Jolliffe, I.T., Uddin, M., Vines, S.K., Simplified EOFs - three alternatives to rotation (2002) Climate Research, 20 (3), pp. 271-279; Kaiser, H.F., The Varimax criterion for analytic rotation in factor analysis (1958) Psychometrika, 23 (3), pp. 187-200; Kaplan, A., Cane, M.A., Kushnir, Y., Clement, A.C., Blumenthal, M.B., Rajagopalan, B., Analyses of global sea surface temperature 1856